# Git push preference

After creating a git commit for meaningful work in this repo, **always push** to `origin` without waiting to be asked.

- **Default branch is `main`.** Bugfixes and placement/combat corrections ship **straight to `main`** (commit on `main` and push). Do not open a feature-branch PR for bugfixes unless the user explicitly asks for a branch/PR.
- Feature branches / draft PRs only when the user asks for a new feature isolation or review-before-merge workflow.
- Still only commit when appropriate (meaningful completed work / when the user expects it).
- Do not force-push to main/master.
- If push fails (auth, conflicts, rejected), report the error and stop.
